Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so\N{\rChinese}好的，接着说：
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.88,0:00:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,last class we talked about Maria Kumbotas,\N{\rChinese}上节课我们讨论了玛丽亚·库姆博塔斯，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.24,0:00:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,who is an anthropologist.\N{\rChinese}她是个古典学者。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.28,0:00:09.54,English,,0,0,0,,And she makes the argument that\N{\rChinese}和她说了个“…”，但…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.54,0:00:12.10,English,,0,0,0,,for the longest time,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.14,0:00:16.10,English,,0,0,0,,for most of its history, Europe was egalitarian,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.46,0:00:18.00,English,,0,0,0,,peaceful,\N{\rChinese}平静，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.46,0:00:22.12,English,,0,0,0,,and artistic. But\N{\rChinese}而且是艺术的。 但…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.12,0:00:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,today, we are a patriarchy.\N{\rChinese}今天，能够了！
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.52,0:00:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of inequality,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.28,0:00:33.52,English,,0,0,0,,and we're always at war with each other.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.82,0:00:35.94,English,,0,0,0,,So what changed? And\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.94,0:00:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,last time we discussed\N{\rChinese}上一次我们讨论
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.36,0:00:41.22,English,,0,0,0,,that\N{\rChinese}那时的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.22,0:00:47.12,English,,0,0,0,,old Europe was conquered by a warlike people,\N{\rChinese}旧的欧陆被战士征服
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.36,0:00:49.68,English,,0,0,0,,who we call today the Yemeniah.\N{\rChinese}谁是我们今天所称的Yemeniah。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.60,0:00:54.14,English,,0,0,0,,So three questions I want to answer in today's class is,\N{\rChinese}三句要回答的题目在此时的班级里。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:55.50,English,,0,0,0,,first of all,\N{\rChinese}第一个是…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.50,0:00:57.86,English,,0,0,0,,who are the Yemeniah?\N{\rChinese}谁是Yemeniah？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.16,0:00:59.50,English,,0,0,0,,Second question is,\N{\rChinese}第二个问题是，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.30,0:01:01.72,English,,0,0,0,,where did they come from?\N{\rChinese}他们来自哪儿？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.26,0:01:05.84,English,,0,0,0,,And the third question is, how did they conquer Europe?\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.26,0:01:08.36,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, so\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.36,0:01:11.74,English,,0,0,0,,let's go back in time\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.74,0:01:17.42,English,,0,0,0,,and look at the world about 10,000 years ago.\N{\rChinese}大约一万年前的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.64,0:01:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,So we believe that about 11,000 years ago, in the Near East,\N{\rChinese}大约一千一百年前的近东地区
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.02,0:01:26.96,English,,0,0,0,,we developed agriculture.\N{\rChinese}我们在近东地区发展了农业
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.96,0:01:30.90,English,,0,0,0,,We developed the technology of farming.\N{\rChinese}我们发明了农耕技术。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.12,0:01:35.46,English,,0,0,0,,And as we discussed in our very first class,\N{\rChinese}而我们在第一堂课里说过的那一段
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.72,0:01:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,it was because humans are a religious people.\N{\rChinese}其后又有个别的…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.22,0:01:44.38,English,,0,0,0,,And farming allows us to celebrate our religion.\N{\rChinese}和农耕让我们得以庆祝我们的宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.08,0:01:49.76,English,,0,0,0,,And the reason why farming was founded in the Near East is,\N{\rChinese}和农耕之于前方的先前方…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.76,0:01:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,for the longest time, there's an ice age.\N{\rChinese}先前方…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.06,0:01:55.26,English,,0,0,0,,So you couldn't farm.\N{\rChinese}所以你们能农耕吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.64,0:02:00.26,English,,0,0,0,,You had to move around from place to place to hunt\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.26,0:02:01.84,English,,0,0,0,,and find food.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.26,0:02:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,So after the ice age, which ended about 12,000 years ago,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.58,0:02:08.88,English,,0,0,0,,the climate became warmer, and\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:12.22,English,,0,0,0,,the Near East became the area where\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.22,0:02:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,you could grow crops, the easiest.\N{\rChinese}你可以种植最简单的作物。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.20,0:02:18.16,English,,0,0,0,,So Near East is what we call the Middle East today,\N{\rChinese}在此处可把“近东”写成“中东”??
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.28,0:02:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,which includes Turkey, Jordan,\N{\rChinese}??
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.14,0:02:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,Syria, and Israel.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.02,0:02:25.54,English,,0,0,0,,That's where farming was invented.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.44,0:02:32.18,English,,0,0,0,,About 7,000, 8,000 years ago,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.28,0:02:35.03,English,,0,0,0,,the weather became a lot cooler.\N{\rChinese}天气变得很凉爽。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:39.28,English,,0,0,0,,There was another ice age for a very short amount of time. And\N{\rChinese}有一个短暂的冰雾之时，...??
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:42.74,English,,0,0,0,,this forced people to start to immigrate\N{\rChinese}...??
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.74,0:02:45.48,English,,0,0,0,,or migrate to look for new land.\N{\rChinese}或迁移到去寻找新土地。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:49.64,English,,0,0,0,,So people in the Near East, they went off to Europe,\N{\rChinese}在近东地区的那一段时间里，先后有个…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:02:54.64,English,,0,0,0,,and these people were very lucky,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.76,0:02:59.40,English,,0,0,0,,because the geography of Europe was not\N{\rChinese}因为欧洲的地理与近东相差不大。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:02.26,English,,0,0,0,,that different from the geography of the Near East.\N{\rChinese}所以能把地理与近东相差不大。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.46,0:03:05.82,English,,0,0,0,,So they could take their religion, they could take their technology,\N{\rChinese}因为地理…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:09.04,English,,0,0,0,,move over to Europe, and\N{\rChinese}移动到欧洲，且…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:11.62,English,,0,0,0,,still be about the same.\N{\rChinese}仍然是同样的…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.72,0:03:12.96,English,,0,0,0,,There were some minor changes,\N{\rChinese}有些小变化…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.60,0:03:15.32,English,,0,0,0,,but they were more or less the same.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.84,0:03:17.26,English,,0,0,0,,So these people were very lucky.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.64,0:03:20.58,English,,0,0,0,,And these people, as Maria Kambuta said,\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.94,0:03:25.26,English,,0,0,0,,these people have the same religion as the people of the Near East.\N{\rChinese}这些人和近东人有同样的宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.56,0:03:29.40,English,,0,0,0,,They worship the Mother Goddess, who gives life to everything.\N{\rChinese}他们的母亲神是个别名，给了我方…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.78,0:03:32.76,English,,0,0,0,,They believe in the ideas of unity.\N{\rChinese}他…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.84,0:03:37.04,English,,0,0,0,,Unity just means that we are the same.\N{\rChinese}统一就是我们相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.22,0:03:38.88,English,,0,0,0,,Every one of us are the same.\N{\rChinese}每个人都一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.00,0:03:42.92,English,,0,0,0,,We have a responsibility to love each other, and to love each other's children.\N{\rChinese}我们有责任相互相爱，互相亲子。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.94,0:03:45.46,English,,0,0,0,,We're the same as animals.\N{\rChinese}我们像动物一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:50.42,English,,0,0,0,,We're the same as plants. So we must do our best to protect nature.\N{\rChinese}我们像植物一样。于是我们要尽力保护自然。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.96,0:03:53.80,English,,0,0,0,,The farms allow us to eat food, but\N{\rChinese}农场让我们吃得吃
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.80,0:03:55.90,English,,0,0,0,,we should not destroy nature.\N{\rChinese}我们不该毁掉自然。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.06,0:03:58.86,English,,0,0,0,,We should protect nature, because it's all the Mother Goddess.\N{\rChinese}我们要把它们放在好处，回到…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,We're all the children of the Mother Goddess.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.96,0:04:06.68,English,,0,0,0,,So we also believe in balance and harmony.\N{\rChinese}我们也相信平衡与和谐。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.98,0:04:09.62,English,,0,0,0,,And this is the religion, as we discussed before,\N{\rChinese}这就是我们之前讨论过的那种宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:13.72,English,,0,0,0,,of many indigenous peoples around the world.\N{\rChinese}许多种古老之人们的宗教。”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:15.36,English,,0,0,0,,If you go to Africa, Australia,\N{\rChinese}如果你去…………………………………………………
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:20.74,English,,0,0,0,,the Amazon, and you meet these indigenous peoples,\N{\rChinese}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:22.82,English,,0,0,0,,they have the same religion,\N{\rChinese}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.92,English,,0,0,0,,which is, we come from a Mother Goddess,\N{\rChinese}哪一是我们来自母神，并且我们有责任去守护自然，地球因为它是母神的礼物。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:30.70,English,,0,0,0,,and we have a responsibility to protect the nature,\N{\rChinese}哪一??……?????
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:35.80,English,,0,0,0,,the earth, because that's the gift from the Mother Goddess.\N{\rChinese}??
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:37.64,English,,0,0,0,,And everyone has a soul.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:42.02,English,,0,0,0,,So after we die, our soul still lives on.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:44.52,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense, guys? So\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.52,0:04:47.60,English,,0,0,0,,this is the religion of old Europe.\N{\rChinese}这是古欧洲的宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:50.00,English,,0,0,0,,And because of this religion, they were egalitarian,\N{\rChinese}因为这宗教，大家都平等。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:53.50,English,,0,0,0,,meaning there was no real difference between men and women.\N{\rChinese}意思是说，男女人都相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.66,0:04:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, because women had the power to give birth,\N{\rChinese}在此，因女子有生育之能，被视为多方面优于男子。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.36,0:05:02.12,English,,0,0,0,,to give life, they were considered in many ways superior to men.\N{\rChinese}在此，因女子有生育之能，其后期可用来回顾
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:06.24,English,,0,0,0,,And the political class was mainly governed by women.\N{\rChinese}??
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.38,0:05:09.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They were peaceful.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们很安静。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.80,0:05:11.86,English,,0,0,0,,They really didn't have to fight each other, because\N{\rChinese}好的，没能很久！
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.86,0:05:15.72,English,,0,0,0,,they felt their resources was enough for them.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:17.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And they were artistic. So\N{\rChinese}好的？他们很有艺术性。于是他们把智力投入到创作艺术来庆祝母神与宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.76,0:05:21.20,English,,0,0,0,,they focused their intellectual energies on\N{\rChinese}好的？把它们的智力投入到创作艺术来庆祝母神！】】\}We need to translate cues 94-96. Provide array of 3 translations. Each translation string may contain at most one newline. Should be natural Chinese. Use terms:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:24.76,English,,0,0,0,,creating art to celebrate the Mother Goddess and their religion.\N{\rChinese}etc. Let's craft. Cue 94:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.98,0:05:28.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the people of the Near East\N{\rChinese}好的？近东的人们和欧洲的人们非常相似。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.38,0:05:30.76,English,,0,0,0,,and the people of Europe were very similar.\N{\rChinese}好的，...??
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:35.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The problem starts when these people went off to\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,what we call the steppes.\N{\rChinese}什么叫作?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,The steppes is a huge ocean of grassland\N{\rChinese}...?????
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:48.18,English,,0,0,0,,that basically extends from Europe into Mongolia.\N{\rChinese}...???
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.50,0:05:51.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And you know, the Chinese word for this is taoyuan.\N{\rChinese}好的？而且，中文里有个“taoyuan”一词。”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:55.84,English,,0,0,0,,Now the problem with the\N{\rChinese}现在………………
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.84,0:05:59.04,English,,0,0,0,,grassland is people can't eat grass.\N{\rChinese}“草地”草地??
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,And you cannot grow crops on grassland\N{\rChinese}在草原上种植作物很难，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.60,0:06:04.94,English,,0,0,0,,that easily. Okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,So the people on the steppes,\N{\rChinese}在草原里…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.76,0:06:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,they struggle to survive.\N{\rChinese}他们在草原上挣扎求存。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.72,0:06:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,And the people on the steppes\N{\rChinese}草原里的那一群人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.64,0:06:20.16,English,,0,0,0,,engage in a process we call social evolution.\N{\rChinese}草原里的人们在做着…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So you may have heard the term evolution.\N{\rChinese}好的？你可能已经听过“演化”这个词。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.76,0:06:30.04,English,,0,0,0,,I want to explain what the term evolution means for our class,\N{\rChinese}我想给你们说一段关于“演化”在本班的好时机。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.26,0:06:34.82,English,,0,0,0,,because we will refer to it a lot as we progress through human history.\N{\rChinese}先前…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.90,0:06:39.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So for us, evolution means open\N{\rChinese}好的？所以对我们来说，演化意味着开放协作竞争。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:46.10,English,,0,0,0,,cooperative competition.\N{\rChinese}好的，演化就是开放协作竞争。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.08,0:06:52.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this is what evolution means.\N{\rChinese}好的，演化…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.38,0:06:53.34,English,,0,0,0,,And\N{\rChinese}和
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,evolution has historically been the\N{\rChinese}演化在历史上是人类创新与创造力的最大来源。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.40,0:07:01.20,English,,0,0,0,,greatest source of human innovation and creativity.\N{\rChinese}greatest source of humaninnovation and creativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:03.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So let me explain why.\N{\rChinese}好的？让我来解释一下原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.36,0:07:07.98,English,,0,0,0,,Open means there's no central authority.\N{\rChinese}开放意味着有一个无中心的管理。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:09.74,English,,0,0,0,,There's no great power.\N{\rChinese}还有一个大国的缺失。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.90,0:07:13.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There's no hegemon. Everyone's competing against each other.\N{\rChinese}好的？没有霸权。大家相互竞争。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.04,0:07:17.02,English,,0,0,0,,Competition just means these people,\N{\rChinese}竞争只是意味着这些人，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.66,0:07:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,these many different people, they're trying to compete to survive.\N{\rChinese}这些多种多样的人，他们正试图竞争以求生存。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.36,0:07:26.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There are very scarce resources in the steppes.\N{\rChinese}好的？在草原里资源很稀缺。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.88,0:07:29.78,English,,0,0,0,,It's not as wealthy as the Near East and as Europe.\N{\rChinese}它不如近东和欧洲那么富裕。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.00,0:07:31.40,English,,0,0,0,,And they're all trying to survive.\N{\rChinese}他们都在努力生存。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:35.00,English,,0,0,0,,They all adopt different strategies in order to survive.\N{\rChinese}他们各自采用不同的策略以求生存。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.32,0:07:37.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? At the same time,\N{\rChinese}好的吗？与此同时，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:42.14,English,,0,0,0,,cooperative means they're still communicating with each other.\N{\rChinese}合作意味着他们仍在互相交流。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.28,0:07:44.70,English,,0,0,0,,They're still trading. They're still friends.\N{\rChinese}他们仍在交易。他们仍是朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:47.78,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe they'll exchange wives,\N{\rChinese}也许他们会交换妻子，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.14,0:07:50.40,English,,0,0,0,,exchange presents. So\N{\rChinese}再交换礼物。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:55.46,English,,0,0,0,,this is a process of social evolution\N{\rChinese}这是一种社会演进过程，已产生人类最大发创新。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.46,0:07:59.30,English,,0,0,0,,that has created the most innovation in human history.\N{\rChinese}这是一种…………
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.52,0:08:01.22,English,,0,0,0,,So in Chinese history,\N{\rChinese}? 1? 1..??? ??..??? 1..??..
